                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-11T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 11, 1931—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Your 34, April 10, 5 p.m. Question of ratification is being considered by the
                    President but no action can be taken before April 15. A comprehensive
                    instruction in regard to the matter will be sent to you in the near future.
                    Should you find it necessary to make some answer to the Austrian authorities as
                    to when the Legation will be prepared to exchange ratifications, you should
                    confine your answer to a statement that you are awaiting instructions in the
                    premises.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
